rComments: BEST PROFESSOR!!!! Everyone loved her, she is very good at creating a positive learning environment. I learned ALOT from her! She is not an easy marker but she is fair!
She was the most redeeming part of the MSW program. Even if she is not the easiest marker, you like her and learn so much it eases the blow.

Marion is AMAZING. If you ever get a chance to take a class with her, do it. Approachable, very knowledgeable (wrote the book, literally) and fair. It was honestly the best learning experience I've ever had, and I wish I could do it again.

Great class - you'll get to know everyone really well. She's wonderful and setting a good tone and a comfortable environment. Great interactive activities and opportunities for feedback. The Elements and Lab course is are most useful courses you'll take in the program. Excellent prof.

Marion Bogo is an incredible professor who has a true gift for teaching. Her ability to link students' experiences to  social work concepts and skills brings "theory in practice" to life. Not to mention she is the most adorable and heartwarming lady! Most highly recommended.

Bogo is a really good prof and is clear on what she expects. Just don't get on her "bad side". Be on time for class and don't talk when she's talking! She has a lot of experience in the field and that comes across in her classes.
Amazing prof! Listens to the students' needs. Very approachable and understanding. She makes the learning material very interesting. If only FSW had more prof like her!
